<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>scellrun — scRNA QC report</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif; max-width: 980px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 0 1rem; color: #222; line-height: 1.55; }
  h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; border-bottom: 2px solid #333; padding-bottom: .3rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: .5rem 0 1.5rem; font-size: .92rem; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: .35rem .55rem; text-align: right; }
  th:first-child, td:first-child { text-align: left; }
  thead { background: #f6f6f6; }
  .kv { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: .25rem .8rem; margin: .5rem 0 1rem; }
  .kv dt { color: #666; }
  .rationale { background: #fafaf6; border-left: 3px solid #c7b07a; padding: .6rem .9rem; margin: .6rem 0; font-size: .92rem; }
  .rationale strong { color: #5a4710; }
  footer { color: #888; font-size: .82rem; margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: .7rem; }
  code { background: #f0f0f0; padding: .05rem .3rem; border-radius: 3px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>scRNA-seq QC report</h1>

<h2>Summary</h2>
<dl class="kv">
  <dt>Cells in</dt>          <dd>{{ "{:,}".format(result.n_cells_in) }}</dd>
  <dt>Cells passing QC</dt>  <dd>{{ "{:,}".format(result.n_cells_pass) }} ({{ "%.1f"|format(100 * result.n_cells_pass / result.n_cells_in) }}%)</dd>
  <dt>Cells flagged out</dt> <dd>{{ "{:,}".format(n_cells_dropped) }}</dd>
  <dt>Genes in</dt>          <dd>{{ "{:,}".format(result.n_genes_in) }}</dd>
  <dt>Genes after min_cells filter</dt><dd>{{ "{:,}".format(result.n_genes_after_filter) }}</dd>
  <dt>pct_mt — median</dt>   <dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(result.pct_mt_median) }}%</dd>
  <dt>pct_mt — 95th pctile</dt><dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(result.pct_mt_p95) }}%</dd>
  <dt>pct_hb — median</dt>   <dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(result.pct_hb_median) }}%</dd>
  <dt>Doublets flagged</dt>  <dd>{{ "{:,}".format(result.n_doublets_flagged) }}</dd>
  <dt>Input matrix shape</dt><dd>{{ raw_counts_check }}</dd>
</dl>

{% if raw_counts_check == "looks_like_normalized" %}
<div class="rationale" style="background:#fff5f5; border-left-color:#c25;">
  <strong>Heads-up:</strong> input matrix looks log-normalized rather than raw counts.
  pct_counts_* numbers are computed but not directly comparable to a raw-count
  cohort, and doublet flagging was skipped (scrublet expects raw counts).
  Re-run on the raw matrix if you want canonical metrics.
</div>
{% endif %}

<h2>Thresholds applied</h2>
<dl class="kv">
  <dt>species</dt>            <dd>{{ thresholds.species }}</dd>
  <dt>min_genes / max_genes</dt><dd>{{ thresholds.min_genes }} / {{ thresholds.max_genes }}</dd>
  <dt>min_counts</dt>         <dd>{{ thresholds.min_counts }}</dd>
  <dt>max_pct_mt</dt>         <dd>{{ thresholds.max_pct_mt }}%</dd>
  <dt>max_pct_ribo</dt>       <dd>{{ thresholds.max_pct_ribo }}%</dd>
  <dt>max_pct_hb</dt>         <dd>{{ thresholds.max_pct_hb }}%</dd>
  <dt>min_cells_per_gene</dt> <dd>{{ thresholds.min_cells_per_gene }}</dd>
  <dt>flag_doublets</dt>      <dd>{{ thresholds.flag_doublets }}</dd>
</dl>

<div class="rationale">
  <strong>Why these defaults?</strong> mt% ceiling is set to 20% rather than the textbook 10% because synovial / cartilage tissue is dissociation-stressed, and 10% silently kills real chondrocytes (PI cohort experience, OARSI working group 2024–2026). For snRNA, the ceiling drops to 5% — anything higher means cytoplasmic carry-over.<br>
  Doublets are <em>flagged</em>, never auto-filtered. Pick a threshold from the score histogram.
</div>

<h2>Per-metric distribution (cells)</h2>
{{ metrics_html | safe }}

<h2>Next step</h2>
<p>
  Inspect the per-cell CSV next to this report (<code>per_cell_metrics.csv</code>). When you're happy with the cuts, load <code>qc.h5ad</code> in scanpy and subset on <code>obs.scellrun_qc_pass</code>: <code>adata = adata[adata.obs.scellrun_qc_pass]</code>. v0.2 <code>scellrun scrna integrate</code> will read <code>qc.h5ad</code> directly from this directory.
</p>

<footer>
  Generated by scellrun — early alpha. Defaults reflect a clinician-bioinformatics working practice. They are <em>opinionated</em>, not neutral; substitute your own when domain demands.
</footer>

</body>
</html>
